div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington.
In the Matter of the Application of Martin DeWall for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the United States District Court Western District of Washington
In the Matter of the Application of MARTIN DeWALL, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
The above named applicant and petitioner, by his attorneys, having stipulated herein with the respondent, through his attorney, for the denial of the writ in the above entitled case, it is

CONSIDERED AND ORDERED, That the writ in the above entitled case, now under advisement by the Court, be denied, the case being admittedly similar to the case of Samuel H. Dixon, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, No. 4346, and the case of Charles Bernat, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, No. 4350, which writs were denied.
Done in open court this 28 day of January, 1919.
